back to its original shape.

00:23:34.330 --> 00:23:37.330 align:middle line:84%
I screwed up the
memory of that metal.

00:23:37.330 --> 00:23:40.220 align:middle line:84%
It didn't go back to
its original shape.

00:23:40.220 --> 00:23:45.770 align:middle line:84%
So I must be violating some
kind of a law of physics

00:23:45.770 --> 00:23:47.930 align:middle line:84%
by changing a
molecular structure.

00:23:47.930 --> 00:23:56.020 align:middle line:84%
Now, having said all this,
maybe I'm totally wrong.

00:23:56.020 --> 00:23:58.570 align:middle line:90%
Maybe this is not it.

00:23:58.570 --> 00:24:05.510 align:middle line:84%
Maybe I'm deriving
or I'm extracting

00:24:05.510 --> 00:24:11.450 align:middle line:84%
